This paper is about compressed domain image classification using a neural network approach. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) as well. Additionally, the paper involves the use of binary sensing patterns, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method, which could be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE).
